04:06.663 --> 04:07.205
Oh, my.

04:07.288 --> 04:08.289
(<i> chuckles nervously</i> )

04:08.373 --> 04:12.251
(<i> with deep voice</i> ):
Oh, such a naughty bird.

04:12.335 --> 04:14.462
{\an1}Turdy!

04:14.545 --> 04:15.505
{\an1}Excuse me.

04:15.588 --> 04:16.839
(<i> Turdy shrieks</i> )

04:18.216 --> 04:20.885
Turdy, what are
you doing?

04:20.969 --> 04:23.012
Turdy?!

04:23.096 --> 04:24.681
(<i> Rocko screams</i> )

04:24.764 --> 04:26.516
Oh, my gosh!

04:26.599 --> 04:27.016
I'll get him!

04:27.100 --> 04:29.185
Come here, you.

04:29.269 --> 04:29.310
(<i> straining</i> )

04:31.980 --> 04:33.147
Heffer, no!

04:33.231 --> 04:33.982
Whoa!

04:34.065 --> 04:35.483
(<i> screams</i> )

04:36.818 --> 04:39.737
(<i> rumbling</i> )

04:45.118 --> 04:45.743
{\an1}MAN:
Hey, you.

04:45.827 --> 04:48.371
That your bird?

04:48.454 --> 04:49.288
Yes.

04:49.372 --> 04:53.293
Well, keep him away
from my monkey!

04:55.628 --> 04:56.045
Oh, yeah?

04:56.129 --> 04:57.547
(<i> clunking</i> )

04:57.630 --> 04:58.756
{\an3}Ouch.

04:59.340 --> 05:01.384
(<i> crashing on TV</i> )

05:01.467 --> 05:03.511
(<i> shrieks</i> )

05:03.594 --> 05:04.512
(<i> doorbell rings</i> )

05:05.805 --> 05:08.850
I thought I told you

05:08.933 --> 05:13.771
{\an1}to keep your bird
away from my monkey.

05:13.855 --> 05:16.232
But he's in his cage
right over there.

05:16.315 --> 05:17.984
(<i> shrieks</i> )

05:18.067 --> 05:19.444
Don't toy with me!

05:22.238 --> 05:23.322
{\an3}Jinky.

05:23.406 --> 05:25.241
And don't come back!

05:28.453 --> 05:29.412
(<i> doorbell rings</i> )

05:29.495 --> 05:30.913
If it's that monkey guy...

05:30.997 --> 05:32.582
(<i> doorbell rings</i> )

05:32.665 --> 05:32.874
Is this yours?

05:32.957 --> 05:34.542
No.

05:34.625 --> 05:35.543
I mean yes.

05:35.626 --> 05:39.672
{\an1}Well, it seems Polly here
got into a gas pump.

05:39.756 --> 05:41.632
{\an3}Oh.

05:51.225 --> 05:53.102
He scared my kid.

05:53.186 --> 05:55.772
He ruined my car.

05:55.855 --> 05:56.981
He chewed my garden.

05:57.065 --> 06:00.985
He pecked my customers.

06:01.069 --> 06:03.529
He ate my pony.

06:03.613 --> 06:04.614
(<i> burps, pony neighs</i> )

06:04.697 --> 06:06.908
He ripped my socks.

06:07.366 --> 06:08.993
(<i> shrieks</i> )

06:11.370 --> 06:12.663
(<i> shrieks</i> )

06:13.122 --> 06:14.957
(<i> shrieks</i> )

06:15.041 --> 06:17.960
Look, bird,
you are pushing my buttons.

06:18.044 --> 06:19.420
You've been nothing
but a nuisance.

06:19.504 --> 06:20.838
Now, get off my nose!

06:20.922 --> 06:23.091
Shoo!

06:23.174 --> 06:24.717
(<i> screams</i> )

06:26.886 --> 06:28.262
{\an1}Turdy, you will
sit still

06:28.346 --> 06:30.973
{\an1}and let me watch
<i>The Fatheads.</i>

06:31.057 --> 06:33.643
Do you hear me?

06:33.726 --> 06:36.646
(<i> screams</i> )

06:37.730 --> 06:40.399
(<i> toilet flushes</i> )

06:44.487 --> 06:46.614
Whoo-hoo!

06:46.697 --> 06:47.824
Whoo.

06:49.242 --> 06:50.493
Whoo.

06:52.078 --> 06:53.121
Whoo.

06:55.081 --> 07:00.294
(<i> both screaming</i> )

07:00.378 --> 07:01.712
Get it off me!

07:01.796 --> 07:03.714
Get it off me!

07:03.798 --> 07:06.175
(<i> screaming</i> )

07:06.259 --> 07:06.843
ROCKO:
Heffer, hold still.

07:06.926 --> 07:08.845
(<i> popping</i> )

07:08.928 --> 07:10.930
(<i> Heffer screams</i> )

07:12.056 --> 07:15.977
Heffer... he's...

07:16.060 --> 07:17.854
{\an1}He's dead.

07:17.937 --> 07:19.522
We killed him.

07:19.605 --> 07:22.066
We killed Filburt's bird.

07:22.150 --> 07:24.986
{\an4}HEFFER:
Rocko, don't even
joke like that.

07:25.069 --> 07:26.696
{\an1}He's fine.

07:26.779 --> 07:27.780
Look at him.

07:33.119 --> 07:33.870
HEFFER:
Chirp, chirp.

07:33.953 --> 07:36.706
I'm fit as a fiddly.

07:36.789 --> 07:38.416
I think
I'll fly away.

07:38.499 --> 07:40.877
No, maybe I'll
sing a song.

07:40.960 --> 07:42.211
No.

07:42.295 --> 07:44.714
Maybe I'll
eat bugs.

07:44.797 --> 07:46.591
Hello, Turdy.

07:46.674 --> 07:48.009
Itty-bitty birdie.

07:49.093 --> 07:49.552
See?

07:49.635 --> 07:50.887
(<i> giggles weakly</i> )

07:50.970 --> 07:51.888
(<i> air deflates</i> )

07:51.971 --> 07:53.222
There you go.

07:53.306 --> 07:56.517
Oh, Heffer,
what are we going to do?

07:56.601 --> 07:58.561
Filburt was so attached
to that bird.

07:58.644 --> 08:00.229
He left it
for us to care for

08:00.313 --> 08:01.731
and we killed it.

08:01.814 --> 08:03.065
{\an1}How can I
replace it?

08:03.149 --> 08:05.401
I'm just going
to have to tell him.

08:05.484 --> 08:07.278
{\an4}HEFFER:
Rocko, come
in here quick!

08:09.530 --> 08:11.824
{\an1}Whoo, now you're
dirty cool.

08:11.908 --> 08:13.284
{\an1}Surf's up!

08:15.912 --> 08:19.081
ROCKO:
Heffer, the bird is dead.

08:19.165 --> 08:24.253
This is something
you're going to have to accept.

08:24.337 --> 08:27.423
HEFFER:
No!

08:27.506 --> 08:29.050
(<i> sobbing</i> )

08:29.133 --> 08:31.969
Heffer, please listen.

08:32.053 --> 08:34.138
No, I won't
believe it.

08:34.222 --> 08:36.974
Look here in the book.

08:37.058 --> 08:39.559
{\an5}ROCKO AND HEFFER:
"How to tell if your bird
is dead."

08:41.604 --> 08:42.813
Mm-hmm.

08:43.188 --> 08:45.441
Oh, yeah.

08:45.524 --> 08:46.776
(<i> flies buzzing</i> )

08:46.859 --> 08:47.318
{\an3}Mm-hmm.

08:47.401 --> 08:49.612
He's dead all right.

08:49.695 --> 08:50.112
(<i> tires screech</i> )

08:50.196 --> 08:51.697
It's the monkey guy!

08:53.616 --> 08:53.824
Filburt!

08:53.908 --> 08:55.534
Hello.

08:55.618 --> 08:59.330
Oh, Rocko, terrible news.

08:59.413 --> 09:00.456
Oh?

09:00.539 --> 09:03.960
The doctors couldn't find
anything wrong with me.

09:04.043 --> 09:04.460
Fools.

09:04.543 --> 09:06.212
(<i> hawks, spits</i> )

09:06.837 --> 09:09.674
Oh, Filburt, I'm sorry.

09:09.757 --> 09:10.800
Maybe next time.

09:10.883 --> 09:12.718
Aah, whatever.

09:12.802 --> 09:17.348
Now, where's
my precious Turdy?

09:17.431 --> 09:18.975
Um...

09:19.058 --> 09:21.644
Should I sit down?

09:21.727 --> 09:22.979
Yes.

09:23.062 --> 09:25.106
{\an1}Filburt, um...
this is...

09:25.189 --> 09:25.856
(<i> chuckles nervously</i> )

09:25.940 --> 09:28.276
{\an1}This is very hard
for me to say.

09:28.359 --> 09:30.569
The bird is dead, isn't it?

09:30.653 --> 09:31.821
Eh...

09:31.904 --> 09:33.823
Yes.

09:33.906 --> 09:36.200
Oh, Rocko.

09:36.284 --> 09:38.286
Now, Fil, please...

09:38.369 --> 09:40.329
{\an5}I should have
said something
before I left.

09:40.413 --> 09:42.873
Turdy belonged
to a species

09:42.957 --> 09:44.542
known as
<i>Tirdius minimus,</i>

09:44.625 --> 09:48.170
{\an1}a rare subfamily of mynah with
only a three-week life-span.

09:48.254 --> 09:51.424
I'm surprised he lived
as long as he did.

09:51.507 --> 09:54.927
Sure, he was like family,
and I'm going to miss that,

09:55.011 --> 09:55.511
but life goes on.

09:55.594 --> 09:57.722
But, Filburt, you see...

09:57.805 --> 10:00.057
Don't worry
about it.

10:00.141 --> 10:02.143
{\an1}Did you tell him
I sat on it?

10:04.645 --> 10:06.939
FILBURT:
I'm so glad we did this.

10:07.023 --> 10:10.359
Turdy always told me
he wanted to be buried at sky.

10:18.409 --> 10:20.119
Now I think
it would be a good idea

10:20.202 --> 10:22.872
if we all said something.

10:22.955 --> 10:24.373
{\an3}Heffer?

10:24.457 --> 10:27.043
Would you like
to say something?

10:27.126 --> 10:28.294
Um...

10:28.377 --> 10:30.129
Beans, beans,
they're good for your heart

10:30.212 --> 10:31.130
The more you eat...

10:31.213 --> 10:32.548
All right,
that's enough.

10:32.631 --> 10:34.050
Rocko?

10:34.133 --> 10:35.885
{\an1}Would you like
to say a few words?

10:35.968 --> 10:36.552
Um, yes.

10:36.635 --> 10:39.221
Uh... well, let's see, um...

10:39.305 --> 10:40.222
Yeah, uh...

10:40.306 --> 10:42.391
(<i> chuckles nervously</i> )

10:42.475 --> 10:46.395
Turdy was, um...

10:46.479 --> 10:47.355
{\an3}bird.

10:47.438 --> 10:50.733
(<i> wailing</i> )

10:50.816 --> 10:53.027
That's so beautiful.

10:53.110 --> 10:55.780
And I hope that
wherever he is, that...

10:55.863 --> 10:56.906
Okay, my turn.

10:56.989 --> 10:59.700
Turdy, bless you.

10:59.784 --> 11:03.412
Even though you were with us
for a brief time,

11:03.496 --> 11:08.793
you still had plenty of time
to spread happiness.

11:08.876 --> 11:09.877
(<i> sighs</i> )

11:13.881 --> 11:15.091
Let's get some tacos.

11:15.174 --> 11:16.175
{\an1}Yeah!

11:16.258 --> 11:17.760
{\an1}Whoo-hoo!

11:17.843 --> 11:20.679
{\an1}Whoa...

11:20.763 --> 11:22.306
(<i> screams</i> )

11:22.723 --> 11:24.475
{\an1}(<i> crash</i> )

11:28.437 --> 11:28.979
{\an1}Hey, you.

11:29.063 --> 11:31.732
Bird boy.

11:31.816 --> 11:33.359
ALL:
Yes?

11:33.442 --> 11:35.653
Here, this is yours.

11:35.736 --> 11:37.905
I ain't dealing with it.

11:37.988 --> 11:40.783
ALL:
All right!

11:40.866 --> 11:41.951
{\an1}HEFFER:
Food!

11:42.034 --> 11:43.452
Old silverware!

11:43.536 --> 11:44.954
FILBURT:
Hey, monkey,

11:45.037 --> 11:45.621
you little
sweetheart.

11:45.704 --> 11:48.541
What's in
the box? Money?

11:49.291 --> 11:52.920
Oh, my goodness.

11:53.003 --> 11:55.297
Little tiny baby...

11:55.381 --> 11:56.298
monkey birds.

11:56.382 --> 11:59.093
I've got a whole family.

11:59.176 --> 12:02.179
Thank you, Turdy.

12:05.224 --> 12:10.479
And now my first Sunday frolic
with my new family.

12:10.563 --> 12:12.606
Could you give me a push,
Hutch, honey?

12:12.690 --> 12:14.942
You got it, turtledove.

12:16.152 --> 12:18.362
I'm nauseous.

12:18.446 --> 12:20.072
I'm nauseous.

12:20.156 --> 12:21.532
I'm nauseous.

12:21.615 --> 12:21.866
I'm nauseous.

