13:58.128 --> 13:59.463
Hey, everybody!

13:59.547 --> 14:02.091
{\an1}Good day,
junior weasels.

14:02.174 --> 14:05.386
(<i> flatly</i> ):
Good day, senior weasels.

14:05.469 --> 14:07.846
HEFFER:
Hey, Teddy!

14:07.930 --> 14:11.100
{\an1}Great meeting last week
at your house.

14:11.183 --> 14:14.436
Is you mom still
hospital... ized?

14:15.813 --> 14:19.275
Okay, weasels,
now that everyone's here,

14:19.358 --> 14:21.193
let's get the meeting under way.

14:21.277 --> 14:24.363
Our special weasel-graph today
will be model rockets.

14:24.446 --> 14:26.407
ALL:
Hooray!

14:27.408 --> 14:28.951
(<i> click; rumbling</i> )

14:29.034 --> 14:31.078
ALL:
Hooray!

14:31.704 --> 14:33.414
(<i> click; rumbling</i> )

14:33.497 --> 14:35.165
ALL:
Hooray!

14:36.166 --> 14:38.210
(<i> click; loud roaring</i> )

14:40.546 --> 14:43.465
(<i> all scream</i> )

14:43.549 --> 14:44.508
(<i> crash</i> )

14:44.592 --> 14:46.719
(<i> sirens wailing</i> )

14:46.802 --> 14:48.679
{\an5}LEADER:
Well, weasels,
the meeting is adjourned.

14:48.762 --> 14:52.141
Don't forget
this Saturday afternoon,

14:52.224 --> 14:53.475
the all-city Weasel Scout
Jamboree talent show.

14:53.559 --> 14:57.605
The scout troop with the best
act gets to go to Astro Camp.

14:58.897 --> 15:01.483
Why don't you stay home
for that one, Sputnik?

15:01.567 --> 15:05.571
{\an5}LEADER:
And next week we'll have
our meeting at Paul's house.

15:08.073 --> 15:09.575
{\an1}I'm a failure,
Filburt.

15:09.658 --> 15:12.036
{\an1}Nobody in the scouts
likes me.

15:12.119 --> 15:14.663
{\an1}I can't do
anything right.

15:14.747 --> 15:16.248
{\an3}Yeah.

15:16.332 --> 15:18.334
You're probably
right.

15:18.417 --> 15:22.755
But trust me, you're
senior-weasel material.

15:22.838 --> 15:24.798
They just
don't know it.

15:24.882 --> 15:25.924
Cheer up, Hef.

15:26.008 --> 15:26.925
Watch this.

15:28.761 --> 15:33.057
Hey, pal-- get your buns
out of my eyes!

15:33.140 --> 15:34.767
(<i> laughs wildly</i> )

15:34.850 --> 15:38.312
{\an1}"Get your buns
out of my eyes"!

15:39.980 --> 15:40.856
Wait, wait!

15:40.939 --> 15:42.024
I got one! I got one!

15:42.107 --> 15:43.692
(<i> clears throat</i> )

15:43.776 --> 15:46.487
Roses are red, violets are blue

15:46.570 --> 15:48.197
Sugar is sweet...

15:48.280 --> 15:49.698
(<i> slurps</i> )

15:49.782 --> 15:52.743
(<i> belching</i> ):
this belch is for you.

15:52.826 --> 15:59.500
(<i> laughing</i>
<i>hysterically</i> )

15:59.583 --> 16:02.503
That was great.

16:02.586 --> 16:04.296
(<i> laughing</i> )

16:04.380 --> 16:08.175
You ought to do that for
the Weasel Scout talent show.

16:09.635 --> 16:11.595
Yeah? You think so?

16:11.679 --> 16:15.849
You think I could, really?

16:15.933 --> 16:17.309
Yeah, yeah,
of course.

16:17.393 --> 16:19.561
{\an1}Yeah!

16:19.645 --> 16:20.979
I <i> could</i> do it!

16:21.063 --> 16:23.732
I <i> can</i> do it!

16:23.816 --> 16:25.901
{\an1}I'm going
to do it!

16:33.659 --> 16:36.078
(<i> belching</i> ):
Roses are red.

16:36.161 --> 16:40.332
(<i> belching continues</i> ):
This burp is for you.

16:40.416 --> 16:42.376
You talking to me?

16:42.459 --> 16:44.586
I said, "Are you talking to me?"

16:44.670 --> 16:48.298
I am Burp Man;
give me a merit badge.

16:48.382 --> 16:52.970
Give me a merit badge now!

16:53.053 --> 16:55.264
(<i> shouts</i> ):
Heffer!

16:55.347 --> 16:58.183
What the heck does he
do in there all day?

17:03.522 --> 17:07.151
What are still parading around
in that uniform for, huh?

17:07.233 --> 17:09.319
Ma, will you look at our son!

17:09.403 --> 17:11.739
{\an4}MA:
I'm busy
in the kitchen, dear.

17:11.821 --> 17:13.031
(<i> drill whirring</i> )

17:13.115 --> 17:15.826
I'm working my way up
to senior Weasel Scout, Dad.

17:15.909 --> 17:18.454
Aah, Weasel Scout,
schmeasel scout.

17:18.537 --> 17:21.457
Son, when are you going
to graduate from that kid stuff

17:21.540 --> 17:23.500
and go on to do
something important?

17:23.584 --> 17:24.626
You know, be somebody--

17:24.710 --> 17:27.628
like, uh...
like, uh...

17:27.713 --> 17:28.464
(<i> snoring, farting</i> )

17:28.547 --> 17:30.883
Like, uh...

17:30.966 --> 17:32.050
(<i> torch flame roaring</i> )

17:33.135 --> 17:34.845
Well, you know.

17:39.850 --> 17:43.437
(<i> elephant trumpeting</i> )

17:45.647 --> 17:49.067
Gee, guys, I don't know
if I should do this.

17:49.151 --> 17:49.777
Oh, come on, Hef.

17:49.860 --> 17:52.571
{\an1}They'll love it,
trust me.

17:52.654 --> 17:53.322
Love what?

17:53.405 --> 17:55.491
You don't think
it's too gross?

17:55.574 --> 17:56.658
What's too gross?

17:56.742 --> 17:58.577
{\an1}Come on, Rocko,
let's get a seat.

17:58.660 --> 18:00.162
{\an1}What are you going
to do, Hef?

18:00.245 --> 18:01.663
(<i> elephant trumpets,</i>
<i>piano crashes</i> )

18:01.747 --> 18:02.956
I hope
I don't mess up.

18:03.040 --> 18:04.583
(<i> audience applauds mildly</i> )

18:04.666 --> 18:07.127
Filburt, what's so gross?

18:07.211 --> 18:09.838
{\an5}WEASEL LEADER:
Thank you, William,
that was very nice.

18:09.922 --> 18:13.175
And now let's have
a warm weasel welcome

18:13.258 --> 18:15.135
for our next talent:

18:15.219 --> 18:17.721
from Den 1149... Heffer Wolfe.

18:17.805 --> 18:19.306
(<i> all gasp and moan</i> )

18:26.105 --> 18:31.276
(<i> feedback whistles sharply</i> )

18:31.360 --> 18:31.652
Um...

18:31.735 --> 18:34.738
I... I...

18:34.822 --> 18:36.573
I'm going to read a poem.

18:36.657 --> 18:40.327
We'll never get
to Astro Camp.

18:42.246 --> 18:44.373
(<i> slurps, then gulps</i> )

18:44.456 --> 18:45.707
Um...

18:45.791 --> 18:47.417
Roses are violet...

18:47.501 --> 18:49.127
Oh! Wait.

18:49.211 --> 18:50.128
Violets are...

18:50.212 --> 18:52.548
No!

18:52.631 --> 18:53.799
(<i> audience boos and jeers</i> )

18:53.882 --> 18:55.425
You stink!

18:55.509 --> 18:56.885
{\an1}Get off
the stage!

18:56.969 --> 19:00.639
Roses are red, violets are blue

19:00.722 --> 19:02.015
Sugar is sweet...

19:02.099 --> 19:02.933
(<i> gulps</i> )

19:03.016 --> 19:06.144
(<i> belching</i> ):
this belch is for you...

19:06.228 --> 19:11.483
(<i> air rushing</i> )

19:17.114 --> 19:21.994
(<i> all laughing hysterically</i> )

19:29.835 --> 19:33.005
(<i> laughing continues</i> )

19:36.675 --> 19:40.095
HEF'S DAD:
"Oaktown scout belching hit."

19:40.178 --> 19:41.972
"The kids love him"?

19:42.055 --> 19:44.975
{\an5}HEFFER:
Oh, boy,
Astro Camp!

19:45.058 --> 19:46.184
Let's go.

19:46.268 --> 19:48.478
{\an5}(<i> belching</i> ):
Left... left...
left, right, left.

19:48.562 --> 19:53.275
{\an5}(<i> belching continues</i> ):
Left... left...
left, right, left.

19:53.358 --> 19:56.028
Left... left...
left, right, left.

19:56.111 --> 19:57.404
Heffer!

19:57.487 --> 20:00.866
{\an5}ALL (<i> chanting</i> ):
My boots are heavy,
my pants are tight...

20:00.949 --> 20:02.409
{\an1}Heffer!

20:02.492 --> 20:03.285
Yeah, Dad?

20:03.368 --> 20:04.494
{\an1}Come here
a minute!

20:04.578 --> 20:05.871
{\an1}I want to talk
to you.

20:05.954 --> 20:07.998
Wait here--
I'll be back in a jiff.

20:08.874 --> 20:09.708
Hey, Dad.

20:09.791 --> 20:12.169
What's this belching thing
about, huh?

20:12.252 --> 20:13.754
Isn't it great?

20:13.837 --> 20:14.963
Everyone loves it!

20:15.047 --> 20:16.089
I'm a local
celebrity.

20:16.173 --> 20:20.260
I'm somebody, just
like you wanted.

20:20.344 --> 20:22.012
Like <i> I</i> wanted?

20:22.095 --> 20:23.263
I wanted you to be someone--

20:23.347 --> 20:25.182
not a freak!

20:25.265 --> 20:27.601
{\an1}Why don't you just grow up
and be an adult?

20:27.684 --> 20:29.561
A freak?

20:34.858 --> 20:36.735
You guys go ahead without me.

20:36.818 --> 20:38.654
But we're going
to Astro Camp.

20:38.737 --> 20:45.661
I'm not going to another scout
function for as long as I live.

20:45.744 --> 20:48.121
Good-bye.

21:01.593 --> 21:05.389
Okay, who wants to blow up
the next satellite?

21:07.099 --> 21:08.850
This is boring.

21:08.934 --> 21:10.811
I miss Heffer.

21:10.894 --> 21:12.354
{\an3}Me, too.

21:12.437 --> 21:13.522
Yeah.

21:13.605 --> 21:15.315
What are we going to do?

21:22.114 --> 21:24.282
WEASEL:
Hey, what's Teddy doing?

21:24.366 --> 21:27.202
PILOT:
Hey, kid, get away from there!

21:27.285 --> 21:29.037
Hey, don't touch that!

21:29.121 --> 21:32.499
WEASELS:
All right, Teddy!

21:32.582 --> 21:35.085
Yeah!

21:36.795 --> 21:39.047
(<i> loud rumbling</i> )

21:39.131 --> 21:41.299
(<i> crash</i> )

21:41.383 --> 21:43.093
What the...?!

21:46.054 --> 21:46.304
Ma!

21:48.807 --> 21:50.684
Yes, dear.

21:50.767 --> 21:52.894
There's a... a...

21:52.978 --> 21:55.063
There's a bunch
of Weasel Scouts...

21:55.147 --> 21:57.858
WEASELS:
♪ All we are saying ♪

21:57.941 --> 22:02.195
♪ Is give Hef a chance. ♪

22:05.198 --> 22:06.908
Go away.

22:06.992 --> 22:08.493
Go to your homes.

22:08.577 --> 22:11.621
I will be your freak no more.

22:13.540 --> 22:17.002
{\an1}This Heffer belching thing
is getting out of hand.

22:17.085 --> 22:18.795
Hmm.

22:18.879 --> 22:21.214
I seem to remember
a certain someone

22:21.298 --> 22:23.592
who had a few peculiar traits
of his own.

22:23.675 --> 22:25.927
Huh?

22:30.891 --> 22:32.476
(<i> someone makes farting sound</i> )

22:32.559 --> 22:33.685
(<i> makes farting sound</i> )

22:33.769 --> 22:35.937
(<i> giggles</i> )

22:36.021 --> 22:38.774
Oh, of course
I'll marry you.

22:40.567 --> 22:41.610
(<i> sniffles</i> )

22:43.862 --> 22:46.615
(<i> sobbing and sniffling</i> )

22:46.698 --> 22:49.910
{\an1}Son...

22:49.993 --> 22:51.661
(<i> snorts</i> )

22:51.745 --> 22:53.914
{\an1}I... came up here
to apologize.

22:53.997 --> 22:56.124
{\an1}I... I...

22:56.208 --> 22:56.958
I overreacted.

22:57.042 --> 23:00.295
(<i> sniffles</i> )

23:00.378 --> 23:00.796
{\an1}I, uh...

23:00.879 --> 23:03.048
just wanted to say

23:03.131 --> 23:06.802
{\an1}that you're always somebody
in this household,

23:06.885 --> 23:09.429
even if you're nobody.

23:09.513 --> 23:12.307
This belch thing's
okay for now, but...

23:12.390 --> 23:15.477
I want you to grow up to be
something better than that.

23:15.560 --> 23:17.145
You got it?

23:17.229 --> 23:18.855
Okay, Dad.

23:18.939 --> 23:19.981
There's one more thing.

23:20.065 --> 23:24.986
It's, um... it's difficult
for me to talk about.

23:25.070 --> 23:28.073
Let me put it this way.

23:28.156 --> 23:29.533
(<i> makes farting sound</i> )

23:32.577 --> 23:33.537
(<i> chuckles</i> )

23:33.620 --> 23:38.125
(<i> both laughing boisterously</i> )

23:40.335 --> 23:43.088
Weasels!

23:43.171 --> 23:46.091
(<i> belching</i> ):
Give me a merit badge now!

23:46.174 --> 23:49.845
WEASELS (<i> cheering</i> ):
Yay! Hooray!

23:49.928 --> 23:51.763
Huh?

23:51.847 --> 23:53.140
Look.

23:55.267 --> 23:57.185
{\an5}WEASEL:
Quick, weasels,
a citizen in need!

23:57.269 --> 24:00.397
(<i> excitedly</i> ):
Lady, here we come!

24:00.480 --> 24:02.274
Weasels are
on the job!

24:04.943 --> 24:06.528
